00:43:06.020 --> 00:43:09.584
FELIPE POMBO: Like, a main
characteristic of all this

00:43:09.584 --> 00:43:10.500
that you could apply--

00:43:10.500 --> 00:43:12.309
AUDIENCE: The most
influential eccentricity

00:43:12.309 --> 00:43:15.760
that you've come across that
can be a universal thing

00:43:15.760 --> 00:43:19.710
to take home?

00:43:19.710 --> 00:43:22.490
FELIPE POMBO: Well,
I've maybe repeated it,

00:43:22.490 --> 00:43:28.620
but not being afraid of breaking
the rules that are there.

00:43:28.620 --> 00:43:30.960
And if it means you
have to leave your job

00:43:30.960 --> 00:43:35.460
and you have to start on
your own something and--

00:43:35.460 --> 00:43:38.310
for instance, I get
all the time this idea

00:43:38.310 --> 00:43:40.950
that journalism has to
be fast and that you

00:43:40.950 --> 00:43:44.310
have to give information all
the time and that you have--

00:43:44.310 --> 00:43:46.600
well, I don't want
to go with that.

00:43:46.600 --> 00:43:50.100
And if I have to start
everything and to do my work

00:43:50.100 --> 00:43:54.030
and breaking these rules,
I'm not afraid to do that.

00:43:54.030 --> 00:43:56.760
And that's something I've
learned from these people.

00:43:56.760 --> 00:44:01.380
They're not afraid to be
called crazy, to be called--

00:44:01.380 --> 00:44:04.950
and of course, we know
the success cases.

00:44:04.950 --> 00:44:07.720
We don't know many
of the failure cases.

00:44:07.720 --> 00:44:10.810
But that will be a
clear characteristic--

00:44:10.810 --> 00:44:14.330
not being afraid of
being who you are

00:44:14.330 --> 00:44:17.800
and standing for what you think.

